  <div id="vibration" style=" padding-top: 100px;">
    <p style="color: #d8e476; font-size: 28px; font-family: orgonboldregular; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center;">
      Vibration
    </p>

    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px; font-size: 21px;">
      Rig site surface data provide limited information about downhole vibration. They are valuable when downhole vibration sensors are not available or when the MWD data quality is poor. However, surface detection is limited to axial and torsional vibrations only, as lateral vibration will not propagate to the surface.

      Cyclic torque and RPM and fluctuating standpipe pressure are possible indications of stick-slip.

    </div>

    <div class="center" style="margin-top: 30px;">
      <%= image_tag "solutions/decision_support/vibration.png", style: "margin-top: 10px;" %>
    </div>
  </div>

